<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-523-255  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 523 255.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Oct 11 1990 n1235 p21(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Managing to block computer crime. (attempt to defraud BritishAerospace)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Investigators were able to identify a gang that allegedlyattempted to defraud British Aerospace of 40 million poundssterling.andP;  The fraud involved the company's treasury system, whichprovides financial staff with access to bank accounts around theworld via the Swift banking network.andP;  The incident points out theneed for improvements in the management of computer security,especially in multinational companies.andP;  Treasury systems mustovercome the security shortcomings of small machines and shouldseriously question the use of password-related financial systemsthat are accessed by dial-up lines.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Aerospace PLC (security measures).andO;Topic:     Computer SystemsSecurityEFTSFraudAerospace Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>